Modern HTML Assignment




Q. 1   List out the features of HTML5


Ans.


New Semantic Elements, 
Canvas Element
SVG Support
Audio and Video Support
Form Enhancements
Geolocation API
Local Storage & Session Storage
Offline Capabilities




-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q. 2  What are HTML Entities? List out 5 commonly used HTML entities 


Ans.


HTML Entities are special codes used to display reserved characters in HTML that would otherwise be interpreted as HTML code. They start with & and end with ;.
&lt; – Less than (<)
&gt; – Greater than (>)
&amp; – Ampersand (&)
&quot; – Double quote (")
&nbsp; – Non-breaking space





-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q. 3  Define accessibility in the context of web development. Discuss why it's essential to create accessiblewebsites and how it benefits different user group.

Ans.


Accessibility means making websites usable for everyone, including people with disabilities.

Why It's Essential:
Inclusivity – Supports users with disabilities
Legal Compliance – Meets accessibility laws
Better UX – Improves overall usability
SEO Benefits – Helps with search engine ranking
Wider Reach – More users can access the content

Benefits for User Groups:
Visually impaired – Screen readers, alt text
Hearing impaired – Captions, transcripts
Mobility issues – Keyboard navigation
Cognitive issues – Simple layout, clear text
Mobile users – Responsive, fast-loading sites



-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q. 4  List any 3 ways which help us in improving the accessibility of HTML.


Ans.

Here are 3 ways to improve accessibility in HTML:

Use Semantic HTML Tags
Provide Alt Text for Images
Ensure Keyboard Navigation





