Q. 5   Create a web page that highlights the features of HTML5. Use appropriate semantic tags to structure the content 
       and showcase at least three key features of HTML5 with explanations.



Ans.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>HTML5 Features</title>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>Key Features of HTML5</h1>
        <p>Explore some of the powerful features introduced in HTML5.</p>
    </header>

    <nav>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="#feature1">Semantic Elements</a></li>
            <li><a href="#feature2">Audio & Video</a></li>
            <li><a href="#feature3">Local Storage</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <main>
        <section id="feature1">
            <h2>1. Semantic Elements</h2>
            <p>HTML5 introduces new semantic tags like &lt;header&gt;, &lt;footer&gt;, &lt;article&gt;, and &lt;section&gt; which make the structure of web pages more meaningful and accessible.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="feature2">
            <h2>2. Audio & Video</h2>
            <p>HTML5 allows embedding audio and video files directly using &lt;audio&gt; and &lt;video&gt; tags without relying on third-party plugins like Flash.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="feature3">
            <h2>3. Local Storage</h2>
            <p>With HTML5, web applications can store data locally in the user's browser using localStorage and sessionStorage, improving performance and user experience.</p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 WebTech Insights</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>





