Q. 6   Create a simple web page which has a table. The table must have 2 columns HTML and HTML5. The table should include 
       a minimum of three rows describing the differences between HTML and HTML5.



Ans.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>HTML vs HTML5</title>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <h1>HTML vs HTML5</h1>
        <p>Comparing the key differences between HTML and HTML5.</p>
    </header>

    <main>
        <table border="1">
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>HTML</th>
                    <th>HTML5</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Requires third-party plugins for multimedia support (e.g., Flash for videos).</td>
                    <td>Supports native multimedia elements like &lt;audio&gt; and &lt;video&gt; without plugins.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Uses presentational tags like &lt;font&gt; and &lt;center&gt; for styling.</td>
                    <td>Focuses on semantic elements such as &lt;header&gt;, &lt;footer&gt;, &lt;article&gt;, and &lt;section&gt;.</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Limited support for offline applications.</td>
                    <td> It introduces offline capabilities through localStorage and the Application Cache (Service Workers for advanced use).</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2025 Akshay Kumar</p>
    </footer>

</body>
</html>








